			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">st4rk wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why the 6502 reads twice? One time from the unprocessed carry address and the other from the address after the carry has been processed?<br /></div>Exactly. It doesn't have the time to add the carry to the MSB of the address during the same cycle that it's trying to read. It adds the carry to the MSB of the address during the 4th cycle while it's reading the data bus, and so it then reads from the correct address on the 5th cycle if necessary.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Is there a game that exploit this kind of behavior?<br /></div>I don't know of one on the NES ... but I bet some 2600 games use it at least for the timing variation.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">What are the historical reasons of such behavior?<br /></div>The 6502 was designed to use a very small number of transistors. The additional complexity and cost of making that addition happen was deemed not worth it, at the time.</div>

